{"lemma":"نارٌ","slug":"نارٌ","root":"ن.#.ر","root_slug":"ن-_-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/ن-_-ر","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"نار","root":"نور","pos":"N","occurrence_count":145},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n40720","n40724"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%86%D8%A7%D8%B1%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"fire","examples":[{"text":"فَلَمَّا قَضَىٰ مُوسَى ٱلْأَجَلَ وَسَارَ بِأَهْلِهِۦۤ ءَانَسَ مِن جَانِبِ ٱلطُّورِ نَارࣰا قَالَ لِأَهْلِهِ ٱمْكُثُوۤا۟ إِنِّيۤ ءَانَسْتُ نَارࣰا لَّعَلِّيۤ ءَاتِيكُم مِّنْهَا بِخَبَرٍ أَوْ جَذْوَةࣲ مِّنَ ٱلنَّارِ لَعَلَّكُمْ تَصْطَلُونَ","english":"And when Moses had completed the term and was traveling with his family, he perceived from the direction of the mount a fire. He said to his family, \"Stay here; indeed, I have perceived a fire. Perhaps I will bring you from there [some] information or burning wood from the fire that you may warm yourselves."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"conflagration","examples":[{"text":"النَّار (an-nār)","english":"Hell"},{"text":"شَيْخ النَّار (šayḵ an-nār)","english":"Lucifer"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"gunfire"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From Proto-Semitic *nūr-."},"ipa":["/naːr/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n40720","headword_ar":"نَارَ","root":"nwr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"intrans., in the sense of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^anaAra","text_ar":"اَنَارَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see the latter, in two places.       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naAruwA Aln~aAra","text_ar":"نَارُوا النَّارَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see 5.       -A3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nurotu AlbaEiyra","text_ar":"نُرْتُ البَعِيرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I made a mark upon the camel with a hot iron."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K.) See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naArN","text_ar":"نَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n40724","headword_ar":"نَارٌ","root":"nwr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"a word of which the meaning is well known; (M, K;) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Fire;"},{"kind":"text","text":"not well explained as signifying] the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"flaming,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"blazing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lahiyb","text_ar":"لَهِيب"},{"kind":"text","text":",)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that is apparent to the sense:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) its"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A","text_ar":"ا"},{"kind":"text","text":"is originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nuwayorapN","text_ar":"نُوَيْرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, TA:) it is fem.: (S, M, Msb:) and sometimes masc.: (AHn, M, K:) and the dim. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^anowaArN","text_ar":"اَنْوَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"w","text_ar":"و"},{"kind":"text","text":"because it is the original medial radical, (S,) and with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":"because"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nAr","text_ar":"نار"},{"kind":"text","text":"is fem.: (Msb:) pl. [of pauc.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^anowurN","text_ar":"اَنْوُرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, L,) in the K"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^anowaArN","text_ar":"اَنْوَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [which is a mistake, though this is also said to be a pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nAr","text_ar":"نار"},{"kind":"text","text":",] (TA,) and [of mult.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"niyraAnN","text_ar":"نِيرَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[which is the most common form] (S, M, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nuwrN","text_ar":"نُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AAF, S, M, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"niyarapN","text_ar":"نِيَرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"niyaArN","text_ar":"نِيَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, K,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^anoyaArN","text_ar":"اَنْيَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also occurs, in the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naAru AlA^anoyaAri","text_ar":"نَارُ الاَنْيَارِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in a trad. respecting the prison of hell; this phrase, if correctly related, perhaps meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naAru Aln~iyiraAni","text_ar":"نَارُ النِّيِرَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AnyAr","text_ar":"انيار"},{"kind":"text","text":"being originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^anowaAr","text_ar":"اَنْوَار"},{"kind":"text","text":". (IAth.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aln~aAru","text_ar":"النَّارُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is also applied to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The fire of hell."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) The Arabs say, in cursing their enemies,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aboEada A@ll~`hu daArahumo waA^awoqada","text_ar":"اَبْعَدَ ا@للّٰهُ دَارَهُمْ وَاَوْقَدَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naArFA A^avarahumo","text_ar":"نَارًا اَثَرَهُمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"May God make their abode distant, and kindle a fire after them!"},{"kind":"text","text":"] And it was a custom of Arab women, as related by IAar, on the authority of El-'Okeyleeyeh, when they feared evil from a man, and he removed from them, to kindle a fire behind him, with the view of causing his evil to depart with him. (T.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naAru A@lomuhaw~ili","text_ar":"نَارُ ا@لْمُهَوِّلِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A fire which the Arabs used to kindle, in the time of ignorance, on the occasion of entering into a confederacy: they threw into it some salt, which crackled"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yufaq~iEu","text_ar":"يُفَقِّعُ"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"when the fire burned it: with this they frightened"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one another"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in confirmation of the swearing."},{"kind":"text","text":"(T.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naAru AlHubaAHibi","text_ar":"نَارُ الحُبَاحِبِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"has been explained in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hb","text_ar":"حب"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naArN","text_ar":"نَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies simply"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Heat."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b5-  Also, (tropical:)  [The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fire,"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning] the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"evil, and excitement,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rage,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or war; as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naAy^irapN","text_ar":"نَايِرَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^awoqada naAra AlHarobi","text_ar":"اَوْقَدَ نَارَ الحَرْبِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He kindled the fire of war"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A.) ―         -b6-  Also, (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Opinion; counsel; advice."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, T, K.) So in the trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA tasotaDiyw^uwA binaAri","text_ar":"لَا تَسْتَضِيوُوا بِنَارِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Almu$orikiyna","text_ar":"المُشْرِكِينَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bnAr A^aholi Al$~iroki","text_ar":"بنار اَهْلِ الشِّرْكِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) (tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Seek ye not to enlighten yourselves by the counsel of the polytheists;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e.,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"seek ye not counsel of the polytheists."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, T, A. *) ―         -b7-  Also, (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Any brand,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mark, made with a hot iron, upon a camel;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(As, T, S, M, A, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nuwrapN","text_ar":"نُورَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nuwrN","text_ar":"نُورٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) pl. as above: (M:) or the pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"niyaArN","text_ar":"نِيَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and the pl. of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nAr","text_ar":"نار"},{"kind":"text","text":"that burns is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"niyraAnN","text_ar":"نِيرَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (IAar, Th, T.) The Arabs say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA naAru h`*ihi Aln~aAqapi","text_ar":"مَا نَارُ هٰذِهِ النَّاقَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"What is the brand,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mark, of this she-camel, with which she is burned?"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, S, A. *) And they say, in a proverb,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bijaAruhaA naAruhaA","text_ar":"بِجَارُهَا نَارُهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, S)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Their origin is indicated by their mark with which they are burned."},{"kind":"text","text":"(T.) The Rájiz says,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"Hat~aY saqawoA A=baAlahumo biAln~aAri\n                      \n                     \n                        waAln~aAru qado ta$ofiY mina AlA^uwaAri"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Until,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"so that, they watered their camels because of the brand that they bore: for the fire,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the brand, sometimes cures of the heat of thirst"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (T, S: *) he means, that, when they saw their marks with which they were burned, they left the water to them. (S. For another reading of this verse, see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bi","text_ar":"بِ"},{"kind":"text","text":".) See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"najorN","text_ar":"نَجْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["TA","S","M","Msb","AHn","K","L","AAF","T"]}]},"classical_definitions":{"source":"hawramani","url":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/%D9%86%D8%A7%D8%B1/","headword_ar":"نار","entries":[{"lexicon_id":"dictionary_18","lexicon_en":"Al-Sharīf al-Jurjānī, Kitāb al-Taʿrīfāt (d. 1413 CE)","lexicon_ar":"كتاب التعريفات للشريف الجرجاني","permalink":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/?p=4536#6d5858","body_html":"<span>النار: هي جوهر لطيف محترق.</span>"},{"lexicon_id":"dictionary_1","lexicon_en":"Ibn Manẓūr, Lisān al-ʿArab (d. 1311 CE)","lexicon_ar":"لسان العرب لابن منظور","permalink":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/?p=4536#126936","body_html":"<p>نار: نارَتْ نائِرَةٌ في الناس: هاجَتْ هائجة، قال: ويقال نارت بغير</p><p>همز، قال ابن سيده: وأُراه بدلاً. والنَّؤُورُ: دخان الشحْم. والنَّؤُورُ:</p><p>النِّيلَنْجُ؛ عن ابن الأَعرابي.</p>"}]}}